<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,1266,2010]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Diagnosis.— 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[298,466,1267,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hera">
<emphasis box="[298,466,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Hypatopa hera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[611,707,1267,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limae">
<emphasis box="[611,707,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">H. limae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[761,862,1268,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arxcis">
<emphasis box="[761,862,1268,1291]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">H. arxcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in facies but differs from the latter two by having a wider uncus; a more widely serrate margin of the proximal flange of the dorsal part of the valva; a more bulbous base of the phallus; and a narrower base of the anellus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[768,853,1339,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hera">
<emphasis box="[768,853,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">H. hera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has a straight digitate process of the dorsal part of the valva that is lacking in 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[483,579,1374,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limae">
<emphasis box="[483,579,1374,1399]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">H. limae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[634,744,1375,1399]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[634,740,1375,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arxcis">H. arxcis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,1266,2010]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Description.—Head: Vertex and frontoclypeus pale brown. Outer surface of labial palpus pale brown intermixed with few brown scales, inner surface pale brown. Antennal scape and pecten pale brown, flagellum brown basally gradually brightening apically. Proboscis pale brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,1266,2010]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Thorax: Tegula and mesonotum pale brown. Legs pale brown. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1144,1518,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 360 – 367" captionStartId="215.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,187,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@215.[151,1436,165,1912]" captionTargetPageId="215" captionText="FIGURES 360 – 367. Imagos of Blastobasinae. 360, Hypatopa pica, holotype. 361, Hypatopa hecate, holotype. 362, Hypatopa acus, holotype. 363, Hypatopa crux, holotype. 364, Hypatopa limae, holotype. 365, Hypatopa hera, holotype. 366, Hypatopa arxcis, holotype. 367, Hypatopa caedis, holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247458/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Fig. 
<number box="[1097,1144,1518,1542]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="365.0">365</number>
</figureCitation>
): Length 5.5 mm (n = 
<number box="[1405,1418,1518,1542]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="1.0">1</number>
), pale brown. Undersurface brown. Hindwing: Translucent pale brown [specimen worn].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="91.[151,1437,1266,2010]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Abdomen: Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[507,676,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 153 – 158" captionStartId="178.[151,264,1966,1989]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,196,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@178.[151,1436,193,1945]" captionTargetPageId="178" captionText="FIGURES 153 – 158. Male genitalia of Blastobasinae. 153 – 154, Hypatopa crux (slide 2041). 155 – 156, Hypatopa limae (slide 2691). 157 – 158, Hypatopa hera (slide 2667)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247420/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
Figs. 
<number box="[573,676,1590,1614]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="157.5" valueMax="158.0" valueMin="157.0">157–158</number>
</figureCitation>
): Uncus narrowed from widened base to subapical region, acutely downcurved and narrowly rounded apically, sparsely setose, shorter than width of anal opening. Gnathos, narrow ring, confluent with tegumen, ventroposterior margin narrowly emarginate mesially. Sockets of tergal setae not extending beyond midlength of tegumen. Valva divided; ventral part basally protracted inwardly, gradually widened to near middle, abruptly narrowed apically to area beneath base of inwardly curved, spinelike process; process setose on outer surface, planate on inner surface; ventral margin sparsely setose; dorsal part with apical portion of costa extending dorsolaterally, forming setose digitate process; basal ridge of digitate process extending ventrally fusing with dorsal ridge of proximal flange; flange ellipsoid, bearing densely packed microtrichiae on upper 
<number box="[230,245,1878,1902]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[255,268,1878,1902]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="3.0">3</number>
, densely packed spinelike setae on lower 
<number box="[792,803,1878,1902]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[815,830,1878,1902]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" value="3.0">3</number>
; margin widely serrate. Juxta bandlike. Vinculum semicircular. Phallus and sclerite of phallus longer than valva; phallus straight, bulbous basally, sclerite of phallus sigmoid-shaped; anellus gradually narrowed from base, apex shallowly notched mesially, setose along midregion. Female Genitalia: Unknown.
</paragraph>
